IRS990.Desc: RESIDENT CAMP:CAMP JORN YMCA HAS MADE A COMMITMENT TO ENSURE A POSITIVE AND SAFE CAMPING EXPERIENCE FOR EACH CHILD WHO ATTENDS OUR SUMMER PROGRAM. OUR FOCUS ON CHARACTER DEVELOPMENT HELPS YOUTH TO GROW IN THE AREAS OF OUR 4 CORE VALUES CARING, HONESTY, RESPECT AND RESPONSIBILITY. CAMPERS CHOOSE 4 INSTRUCTIONAL CLASSES FOR THE WEEK ENSURING GROWTH, PROGRESSION, AND COMPETENCE. DAYS ARE ROUNDED OUT WITH CABIN ACTIVITIES SUCH AS TUBING, SAILING, CABIN CHALLENGES, SPORTS AND MUCH MORE. EVENINGS ARE A TIME FOR EVERYONE TO COME TOGETHER FOR ALL-CAMP ACTIVITIES SUCH AS CAMPFIRES, SKITS, GROUP GAMES, ETC. EACH CABIN GROUP WILL ALSO PARTICIPATE IN A COOK OUT OR OVERNIGHT ON OR NEAR CAMP JORN. CAMPERS COULD COME FOR 1 OR 2-WEEK PROGRAMS.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: CHILD CARE:LOCATED ON THE CAMP JORN YMCA PROPERTY, THE ORGANIZATION OFFERS A FULL DAY, YEAR-ROUND STATE LICENSED CHILD CARE PROGRAM USING A PLAY-BASED EDUCATION/CURRICULUM WHICH ALLOWS EACH CHILD TO GROW AT THEIR OWN PACE IN THE AREAS OF SOCIAL, EMOTIONAL, PHYSICAL AND ACADEMIC DEVELOPMENT.WARM, CARING, EDUCATED STAFF PROVIDE CARE IN A CASUAL, RELAXED SETTING WHERE THE NEEDS AND INTERESTS OF BOTH CHILD AND PARENT ARE RECOGNIZED. SUMMER CHILD CARE ALSO AVAILABLE BY THE DAY, WEEK OR MONTH. THE CENTER AVERAGES ABOUT 20 CHILDREN PER DAY.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: DAY CAMP:FOR DAY CAMP, CAMPERS HAVE AN OPPORTUNITY TO PARTICIPATE IN ACTIVITIES FROM SPORTS TO CRAFTS, GAMES TO ART, AND EXPERIENCE IT ALL INCLUDING TUBING. DURING 2023, WE AVERAGED 107 UNIQUE CAMPERS PER WEEK OVER 10 WEEKS OF CAMP.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ASSOCIATION ASSESSES WHETHER IT IS MORE-LIKELY-THAN-NOT THAT A TAX POSITION WILL BE SUSTAINED UPON EXAMINATION OF THE TECHNICAL MERITS OR THE POSITION, ASSUMING THE TAXING AUTHORITY HAS FULL KNOWLEDGE OF ALL INFORMATION. IF THE TAX POSITION DOES NOT MEET THE MORE-LIKELY-THAN-NOT RECOGNITION THRESHOLD, THE BENEFIT OF THE TAX POSITION IS NOT RECOGNIZED IN THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. THE ASSOCIATION RECORDED NO ASSETS OR LIABILITIES FOR UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS OR UNRECOGNIZED TAX BENEFITS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE FORM 990 IS PREPARED BY THE ORGANIZATION'S CPA USING INFORMATION PROVIDED BY THE ORGANIZATION. THE FORM 990 IS THEN PRESENTED TO THE FINANCE COMMITTEE BY THEIR CPA. A COPY OF THE FORM 990 IS PROVIDED TO MEMBERS PRIOR TO FILING WITH THE IRS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: A CONFLICT OF INTEREST MAY EXIST WHEN THE INTERESTS OR ACTIVITIES OF ANY DIRECTOR, OFFICER, OR STAFF MEMBER MAY BE SEEN AS COMPETING WITH THE INTERESTS OR ACTIVITIES OF THIS CORPORATION, OR THE DIRECTOR, OFFICER, OR STAFF MEMBER DERIVES A FINANCIAL OR OTHER MATERIAL GAIN AS A RESULT OF A DIRECT OR INDIRECT RELATIONSHIP. ANY POSSIBLE CONFLICT OF INTEREST SHALL BE DISCLOSED TO THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS BY THE PERSON CONCERNED, IF THAT PERSON IS A DIRECTOR OF THE CHAIR OF THE CORPORATION, OR TO THE CHAIR, OR SUCH PERSON OR PERSONS AS HE OR SHE MAY DESIGNATE, IF THE PERSON IS A MEMBER OF THE STAFF. UNLESS REQUESTED TO REMAIN PRESENT DURING THE MEETING, THE PERSON HAVING THE CONFLICT SHALL RETIRE FROM THE ROOM IN WHICH THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS IS MEETING AND SHALL NOT PARTICIPATE IN THE FINAL DELIBERATION OR DECISION REGARDING THE MATTER UNDER CONSIDERATION. HOWEVER, THAT PERSON SHALL PROVIDE THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS WITH ANY AND ALL RELEVANT INFORMATION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: CEO'S SALARY IS DETERMINED BASED UPON PERFORMANCE REVIEW BY BOARD. COMPARATIVE DATA IS REVIEWED BUT ORGANIZATION IS NOT ABLE TO COMPENSATE AT THAT LEVEL.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE AUDIT REPORT AND FORM 990 ARE AVAILABLE ON THE ORGANIZATION'S WEBSITE. THE REMAINING DOCUMENTS ARE AVAILABLE BY REQUEST ONLY.
